main event: A civilian witness observed an unidentified object in the sky near Solvay, New York on 7 April 1966.
interesting points: The witness saw the object for approximately 2 minutes,The object was round, roughly 40-50 feet in diameter and maneuvered at low altitude,The object was illuminated and appeared to be rotating,Additional reports indicate there was also an earlier sighting involving a bright light moving across the sky,The investigation revealed no evidence to confirm the presence of a UFO.
